---
description: Next.js and TypeScript frontend rules
globs:
  - "apps/web/**/*.{ts,tsx}"
  - "packages/ui/**/*.{ts,tsx}"
alwaysApply: false
---

Use TypeScript strict mode.

Authorization is enforced server-side; hiding UI is not authorization.
Never expose provider tokens to the browser.
Do not render raw PII without role authorization and an audited action.
AI-generated content must be labeled.
Aggregates must drill down to evidence.
Show data freshness, sample size, and confidence when they affect interpretation.
Use accessible semantic components and keyboard support.
